author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Graeme Smith lauded South Africa's batting performance against Australia in the World Test Championship final, highlighting Aiden Markram's century and his crucial partnership with Temba Bavuma. Smith emphasized Markram's aggressive scoring and Bavuma's captaincy, which propelled South Africa closer to victory.
title: 'It's been outstanding batting performance': Graeme Smith hails South African batters in WTC Final

author: TNN
description: The Indian Medical Association's Gujarat chapter has appealed to Tata Sons, urging them to extend compensation to medical students affected by the Air India flight crash, similar to what was announced for passengers. The association emphasizes the students' role as future healthcare providers, advocating for their families to receive comparable care and support in light of the tragedy.
title: Plane crash: Hand payouts to kin of medical college victims too, says IMA to Tatas

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Following the tragic crash of Air India Flight AI-171 in Ahmedabad, a Shiv Sena (UBT) leader has raised concerns about potential sabotage and lapses in security and maintenance. Questioning the choice of Ahmedabad and past opposition to the Boeing deal, he called for a thorough investigation.
title: Plane crash: 'Was there any cyber attack by enemy country?' asks Sanjay Raut

author: SUBHASH K JHA
description: Shatrughan Sinha reflects on the fifth anniversary of Sushant Singh Rajput's death, acknowledging the enduring mystery and national impact of the loss. He empathizes with Sushant's struggle as an outsider in Bollywood, drawing parallels to his own early career. Sinha advises aspiring actors to persevere but also set realistic timelines for success, believing Sushant's work already serves as his legacy.
title: 'Saw same josh in Sushant as me': Shatrughan Sinha calls Sushant's death national tragedy

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Team India has commenced preparations for the crucial Test series against England with an intense intra-squad match in Beckenham. Skipper Shubman Gill emphasized maintaining intensity during fielding, while Prasidh Krishna highlighted the importance of game time and the team's camaraderie.
title: Shubman Gill urges intensity ahead of England Tests; watch video

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Iran has declared nuclear talks with the US "meaningless" following Israel's military strike, accusing Washington of complicity, a claim the US denies. Despite the tensions, the US urges Iran to resume negotiations, while US President Trump claims his ultimatum set the stage for the strikes. The scheduled nuclear talks in Muscat are now uncertain.
title: ‘Talks meaningless’: Iran blames US for backing Israel

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: A disturbing video circulating online depicts children dismantling a bridge in Patna, Bihar, by removing nuts and bolts, creating a significant safety risk. This incident has sparked concerns about the quality of construction materials used in Bihar's infrastructure. The incident follows a series of bridge collapses in the state last year, highlighting potential issues with construction practices and oversight.
title: Watch: Kids caught unscrewing Patna bridge - video goes viral

author: TNN
description: Manipur mourns the tragic loss of two cabin crew members, a Kuki and a Meitei, in the Ahmedabad Air India plane crash. This shared grief has momentarily united the communities, transcending ethnic divisions. Amidst the sorrow, there's an outpouring of support and calls for peace, highlighting the preciousness of human life and the need for coexistence.
title: Cabin crew deaths blur Kuki-Meitei divide; ‘angels of the sky unite 2 communities'

author: KUSHAGRA DIXIT
description: Delhi experienced a drop in maximum temperature by up to 6.1 degrees Celsius on Friday, offering slight respite from the intense heat, though high humidity persisted. A change in weather patterns, including a trough line and a western disturbance, brought moisture and thunder activity to northwest India.
title: Temperatures fall in Delhi but why does it still feel like 50.3°C?

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Faf du Plessis showcased incredible athleticism with a stunning catch to dismiss Michael Bracewell during the Texas Super Kings and MI New York match. Despite du Plessis' brilliance and TSK's score of 185/6, Nicholas Pooran's MI New York ultimately chased down the target, overcoming an early setback and securing a victory, fueled by Pollard's explosive hitting.
title: MLC 2025: 40-year-old Faf du Plessis takes blinder in MINY vs TSK; watch video

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Following escalating tensions between President Trump and Elon Musk, the White House has directed the Defense Department and Nasa to scrutinize SpaceX's multi-billion dollar contracts. This review, prompted by Musk's criticisms of Trump, raises concerns about political influence on government spending and national security, particularly regarding SpaceX's role in the "Golden Dome" missile defense system.
title: Trump-Musk feud continues? White House reviews SpaceX contracts post spat: Report

author: PRASHANT RUPERA
description: A family from Vasad, Anand, faced unimaginable tragedy as three members died in the Flight AI171 crash shortly after takeoff from Ahmedabad. Rajnikant Patel, his wife Divya, and sister-in-law Hemangini were en route to London for Dhvani Patel's MBA graduation.
title: Graduation celebration turns to grief: Daughter waits alone in UK as family never arrives

author: etimes.in
description: Television actress Dipika Kakar is now home after a 14-hour surgery for stage 2 liver cancer and an 11-day hospital stay. Discharged on June 12, she shared photos expressing gratitude and announced she is tumour-free after the first treatment phase. Her husband, Shoaib Ibrahim, shared their relief and acknowledged the challenging journey ahead.
title: Dipika Kakar shares first post from hospital after discharge post cancer surgery

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Tensions escalate as Iran launches a new wave of attacks on Israel, dubbed "Honest Promise 3," following Israeli strikes on Iranian nuclear and military facilities. Supreme Leader Khamenei vowed retaliation, stating, "We will not permit them to evade consequences." This follows Israel's "greatest military operations in history" inside Iran, targeting key sites and personnel.
title: Iran launches fresh wave of attack at Israel; 3rd retaliation in 24 hours

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: In October 2026, the ICC and MCC will introduce a new catching rule in cricket, disallowing 'bunny-hop' catches where fielders jump from outside the boundary to touch the ball. Fielders can still push the ball from within the boundary, step out, and dive back in to complete a catch.
title: MCC introduces boundary rule change: What is it and how does it affect the sport?

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Shashi Tharoor requests Union Health Minister JP Nadda's help. He wants more NEET-PG exam centers in Kerala. Students face difficulty choosing Kerala cities. Seats exhausted quickly after website reopened. Tharoor highlights potential distress for students. They might have to travel to other states. NBEMS has applicant data. Tharoor hopes for immediate action to add centers.
title: 'NEET-PG seats exhausted within minutes': Tharoor urges for extra exam centres in Kerala

author: TNN
description: Families of the Air India plane crash victims in Ahmedabad grapple with immense grief and uncertainty as they provide DNA samples for identification. A distraught daughter offered to pay Rs 2 crore to bring back her father, highlighting the emotional toll. Amidst the sorrow, stories of lost loved ones and shattered dreams emerge, underscoring the tragedy's profound impact on families.
title: Plane crash: Daughter says ‘I’ll pay Rs 2 crore to Tata group, just bring my dad back’

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Tensions in the Middle East have escalated as Israel launched extensive airstrikes on Iran, targeting military and nuclear sites. Former US President Trump claimed his ultimatum to Iran set the stage, despite denials from his administration. Iran retaliated with missile strikes on Israeli cities. While praising Israel's operation, Trump insists on no direct US involvement, creating a complex situation.
title: 'Those who spoke bravely are all dead': Trump says he gave Iran 60-day ultimatum

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: That uneasy feeling during your morning walk could signal underlying health issues. Changes in pace, balance, or leg sensations might indicate vitamin deficiencies, heart problems, diabetes, or neurological concerns. Weak muscles, inner ear issues, medications, and arthritis can also affect your stride, so it's important to pay attention and consult a doctor if problems persist.
title: When simple morning walk becomes struggle: What it might be saying about your health

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Iran launched missile and drone strikes on Israel, targeting cities like Tel Aviv and Jerusalem, in retaliation for Israeli military actions. The Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps claimed successful hits on strategic targets, while Israel asserted interceptions and significant damage inflicted on Iranian military assets. Prime Minister Netanyahu warned of further Israeli operations, escalating tensions between the two nations.
title: 'When the last sword strikes': Iran's second salvo on Israel - watch

author: ADVITYA BAHL
description: Ghaziabad police arrested Sagar, his mother, and sister for the murder of Kavita, whose body was found in a suitcase. Sagar initially feigned ignorance, claiming his wife left after a dispute. However, call records revealed his involvement in the conspiracy with his father and brothers, who had already been arrested for the crime.
title: UP woman strangled, stuffed in suitcase: Husband knew of murder plot

author: ABHIJEET PATIL
description: Amidst heavy rainfall warnings in Satara's Mahabaleshwar, Deputy CM Eknath Shinde took a boat ride to reach his Dare village on Friday. Delayed by road from Pune, Shinde opted for a quicker route via Koyna dam backwaters. Despite the rain, he crossed the river by motorboat, followed by a short trek to his village.
title: Eknath Shinde encounters bad weather on way to Dare village, takes boat ride home

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Following a challenging day three in the WTC final, Australian assistant coach Daniel Vettori praised Temba Bavuma and Aiden Markram's resilient partnership. South Africa now needs just 69 runs with eight wickets remaining. Vettori acknowledged the difficulty of taking the remaining wickets and expressed concern over Steve Smith's finger injury.
title: Aus assistant coach hails 'exceptional' Markram, Bavuma as SA near historic win

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Aiden Markram's century has put South Africa in a commanding position in the ICC World Test Championship Final against Australia. Chasing 282, the Proteas ended day three at 213 for two, needing just 69 more runs to win.
title: 'He is someone for the big occasion'; SA batting coach hails Markram

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Ayatollah Ali Khamenei promised retaliation for Israeli strikes. Tehran launched deadly missiles at Israel. Khamenei assured military readiness. He warned of grave consequences for Israel. Benjamin Netanyahu cited major military operations against Iran. He addressed the Iranian people. Iran launched more missiles toward Israeli cities. Explosions rocked Tel Aviv and Jerusalem. Iran threatened further attacks and warned other countries.
title: 'Will bring ruin to Zionist regime', vows Ayatollah Khamenei; Israel says Tehran 'never been weaker'

author: AMIT KUMAR
description: Yashasvi Jaiswal, once guided by Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli, now steps into a senior role for India's Test series in England. With Rohit and Virat absent, the young Indian team, led by Shubman Gill, faces a tough challenge. Coach Jwala Singh emphasizes the need for Jaiswal to balance aggression with caution, anchoring the batting lineup in demanding English conditions.
title: 'With no Rohit or Virat, Yashasvi Jaiswal needs to play sensible cricket in England': Coach

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: A former Boeing quality manager, John Barnett, alleged that the 787 Dreamliner factory suffered from substandard parts and reckless practices, prioritizing speed over safety. Barnett, a vocal critic involved in a legal dispute with Boeing, died by apparent suicide, sparking conspiracy theories.
title: Ahmedabad crash: AI plane was same model dead Boeing whistleblower warned about

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: Iran strikes back 2nd time: Tehran responds to Israel's Op Rising Lion

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Punjab Police is investigating the murder of Sikh activist Gurpreet Singh Hari Nau, allegedly orchestrated by Pro-Khalistan preacher Amritpal Singh. As part of the investigation, Faridkot police have reached out to Tinder, seeking details of an account named 'Amrit Sandhu,' suspected to be linked to Amritpal Singh.
title: Tinder trail: Pro-Khalistan preacher Amritpal Singh spotted on app; Police seeks details

author: TNN
description: Aishwarya Toshniwal, a medical student in Akola, narrowly escaped disaster when an Air India flight crashed near her hostel. From her fifth-floor window, she witnessed the horrifying aftermath of the crash, with flames and debris everywhere.
title: Air India plane crash: Wrapped in blanket, medico walks out of hostel inferno

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Akshay Kumar's 'Housefull 5' box office collections are seeing a dip. The movie earned Rs 6 crore on its eighth day. The total India collection is over Rs 133 crore. The film opened with Rs 24 crore on Friday. Saturday and Sunday earnings were Rs 31 crore and Rs 32.5 crore respectively.
title: 'Housefull 5' BO collection: Akshay Kumar’s comedy film earns Rs 133 cr

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Tensions soared as Iran launched retaliatory missile strikes against Israel, following Israeli attacks on Iranian nuclear and military sites. Explosions rocked Tel Aviv and Jerusalem, prompting air raid sirens and shelter warnings. The IRGC claimed responsibility, asserting successful hits on strategic targets, while Israel maintained its defense systems intercepted many missiles.
title: Iran strikes back Israel; Netanyahu warns 'more is on the way' - How the night unfolded

author: DHANANJAY MAHAPATRA
description: The Supreme Court has ordered the release of Sakshi TV anchor K Srinivasa Rao, arrested for allegedly abetting defamatory statements made by a panelist on his show about Amaravati. Justices Mishra and Manmohan emphasized the importance of protecting journalistic participation and free speech.
title: TV anchor not liable for panelist's statement: Supreme Court

author: NAOMI CANTON
description: In a London park, three British Hindu men of Indian and Sri Lankan descent were brutally attacked after being questioned about their origins. The unprovoked assault by three older men, suspected to be Muslim, left two victims unconscious with severe injuries, prompting a police investigation and raising concerns about religious hatred.
title: UK: Three British Hindus beaten up in London park in racially motivated attack

author: TNN
description: In Khajuwala, Bikaner, a gang posing as occult practitioners allegedly drugged four men with sedatives, leading to three deaths and one hospitalization. The victims were lured with promises of doubled money through black magic, but were instead robbed of cash and valuables estimated at Rs 45–50 lakh. Police are investigating the possibility of internal betrayal among the victims.
title: 3 dead, 1 critical after Bikaner men drugged, looted by fake occultists

author: TIMES NEWS NETWORK
description: Goa's Chief Minister Pramod Sawant, bowing to pressure from coastal MLAs, has assured that cab aggregators like Ola and Uber will not be permitted in the state. This decision comes despite the notification of draft aggregator guidelines.
title: No entry for Ola, Uber cab services in Goa

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: The funeral of prominent businessman Sunjay Kapur, former husband of actress Karisma Kapoor, may face delays due to legal formalities involving his US citizenship, sources close to the family have confirmed. Ashok Sachdev, Sunjay’s father-in-law and father of his current wife Priya Sachdev, told NDTV that the funeral will take place in Delhi.
title: Sunjay Kapur’s funeral may be delayed due to US citizenship

author: H M CHAITHANYA SWAMY
description: In Bengaluru, a BMTC bus driver, Atahar Hussain, alleges he was assaulted by Kavya, a software engineer, after refusing to stop at an undesignated location on Sarjapur Road. Kavya insisted on halting near her office, but Hussain cited traffic regulations and a recently relocated bus stop. The situation escalated when Kavya verbally abused and physically attacked him with her slipper.
title: ‘She took her right slipper and assaulted me’: Woman attacks BMTC driver in Bengaluru

author: VISHAL PATADIYA
description: Arjun Patoliya, 37, tragically died in the AI 171 plane crash, leaving his two young daughters orphaned in London just 18 days after their mother succumbed to cancer. He had traveled to India to fulfill his wife's final wish of having her post-death rituals performed in Gujarat.
title: Ahmedabad plane crash: Girls, 8 and 4, lose mom and dad within 18 days

author: SACHIN PARASHAR
description: Following Israel's unprecedented attack on Iran, India has called for dialogue and diplomacy to resolve the escalating tensions in West Asia. Prime Minister Modi, after a call with Israeli PM Netanyahu, expressed India's concerns and emphasized the urgent need for regional peace and stability.
title: 'Deeply concerned': India urges Iran & Israel to avoid escalation

author: SACHIN PARASHAR
description: The UN General Assembly overwhelmingly passed a resolution demanding an immediate ceasefire in Gaza, with 149 nations voting in favor. India abstained, despite key US allies supporting the resolution, while the US and Israel opposed it. This decision follows India's previous support for similar resolutions and recent reliance on Israeli defense technology during a conflict with Pakistan.
title: India, 18 others abstain; 149 back UN resolution for Gaza ceasefire

author: SAURABH SINHA
description: Following Israel's attack and Iran's airspace closure, flights between India and the West are facing significant disruptions. Air India flights are being diverted or returning to their origin, impacting routes to and from cities like London, New York, and Delhi. With both Pakistan and Iran as no-fly zones, Indian carriers will have to take longer routes to reach Central Asia.
title: Iran airspace shut, international flights from India to take longer
